South Africa has taken a step closer to legalising medical marijuana.Many have been advocating for the drug over the years and former IFP MP Dr Mario Oriani-Ambrosini took it to Parliament during his own fight against terminal cancer, before his death in 2014.News24 sat down with a Johannesburg maker of cannabis oil for chronic illnesses."Making the oil is about trying to help people," she said.Ralph Higgo, founder of cannabis.co.za which dispenses medical marijuana to prescribed patients, says the drug has many success stories.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.